content: अनंग {%<ab>a.</ab>%} [न. ब.] {@--1@} Bodiless, without a body; formless, incorporeal; त्वमनंगः कथमक्षता रतिः <ls>Ku. 4. 9.</ls> {@--2@} Different from the body. {@--3@} Without a supplement or auxiliary. --गः Cupid (the bodiless one; so called from his having been reduced to ashes by Śiva with the fire of his third eye, when he tried to seduce the God's mind towards Pārvatī for the birth of a deliverer of the gods from Tāraka). --गं {@--1@} Sky, air, ether. {@--2@} The mind (आकाशस्य निरवयवत्वात् न्यायवैशेषिकमते चित्तस्य अगुणत्वेन तस्य तथात्वं).
